CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1941, pg. 21, reads: "Cab and 'Rochester' Swing It - Eddie Rochester Anderson (L) and Cab Calloway, famous orchestra leader, held a jive conference and jammed a little at Hill City Auditorium last Friday night. Cab and his orchestra played free. 'Rochester' dropped in after his stage appearance at the Stanley Theatre. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Cab Calloway conducting his orchestra, including Leon "Chu" Berry on saxophone, performing in Hill City Auditorium (Savoy Ballroom)
